  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[160ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>, <strong>coconut stock</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has reduced to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>creamy chickpea & spinach curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the curry is cooking, add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster </strong>for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Tip: For a little extra indulgence, add a little knob of butter to the warmed naan once it's out of the toaster</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chickpea-and-spinach-curry-with-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with the <strong>creamy chickpea & spinach curry</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>warmed naan</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
